net.gini.android.vision.noresults

Class NoResultsFragmentCompat

  • java.lang.Object
    • Fragment
      • net.gini.android.vision.noresults.NoResultsFragmentCompat

  • public class NoResultsFragmentCompat
extends Fragment

    Component API

    When you use the Component API with the Android Support Library, the NoResultsFragmentCompat displays hints that show how to best take a picture of a document.

    Include the NoResultsFragmentCompat into your layout by using the NoResultsFragmentCompat.createInstance(Document) factory method to create an instance and display it using the android.support.v4.app.FragmentManager.

    Your Activity must implement the NoResultsFragmentListener interface to receive events from the No Results Fragment. Failing to do so will throw an exception.

    Your Activity is automatically set as the listener in NoResultsFragmentCompat.onCreate(Bundle).
